Class SparseIndexedFloatList

java.lang.Object
  net.varkhan.base.containers.list.SparseIndexedFloatList
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable, Container<java.lang.Float>, Indexable, Indexed<java.lang.Float>, IndexedCollection<java.lang.Float>, IndexedContainer<java.lang.Float>, IndexedVisitable<java.lang.Float>, IndexedFloatList, IndexedList<java.lang.Float>, FloatIterable, FloatVisitable, IndexedFloatCollection, IndexedFloatContainer, IndexedFloatVisitable, Visitable<java.lang.Float>
public class SparseIndexedFloatList
extends java.lang.Object
implements IndexedFloatList, java.io.Externalizable

IndexedFloatList using sparse segments..

This list stores objects in arbitrary positions (their index, in the sense of Indexed).

The entries are kept in a resizable array of storage segments. Each segment maintains occupancy statistics in a bit array, and a compact array of actual elements.

The segment structure bypasses the normal size limits implied by the int subscript, and limits reallocation costs.
